  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the grill to 400 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together fish sauce, lime juice, garlic, black pepper, and all-purpose seasoning.",
    "Add the sliced pork to the bowl and marinate for at least 30 minutes.",
    "Grill the pork for 5-7 minutes per side, or until it reaches an internal temperature of 145 degrees Fahrenheit.",
    "Let the pork rest for 5 minutes before slicing it thinly.",
    "Assemble the bun thit nuong by placing a few slices of pork onto a talavera plate, followed by a spoonful of pickled carrots and daikon, a few vermicelli noodles, and a sprinkle of chopped cilantro.",
    "Serve immediately and enjoy.",
    "Garnish with additional cilantro and pickled vegetables if desired."
